Module fitnessclubgui.fitnessclub
Package fitnessclubgui.fitnessclub

Class StudioManagerController

java.lang.Object
fitnessclubgui.fitnessclub.StudioManagerController
public class StudioManagerController extends Object
User Interface for software that manages a fitness club. Allows members to be added/removed from the database, for them or guest to attend/be removed from classes, can display the list of members in the club and show the attendees for requested classes. Is a GUI based desktop program.
Author:
Ashley Berlinski, Francisco Marquez

  • Method Details

    • loadMemberFile

      private boolean loadMemberFile(File memberFile)
      Given a text file, loads the list of members to the member's list.
      Parameters:
      memberFile - the file that is attempted to be loaded.
      Returns:
      true if the members list was successfully loaded, false if otherwise.

    • loadSchedule

      private boolean loadSchedule(File scheduleFile)
      Given a text file, loads the list of fitness classes to the schedule.
      Parameters:
      scheduleFile - the file that is attempted to be loaded.
      Returns:
      true if the schedule was successfully loaded, false if otherwise.

    • initializeSchedule

      private void initializeSchedule()
      Helper method, initializes columns in schedule tableview/choicebox and loads the contents of the schedule from the resources' folder. Will print error messages to console if file could not be read or located.

    • initializeMembersTable

      private void initializeMembersTable()
      Helper method, initializes columns in members tableview and loads the contents of the members list from the resources folder. Will print error messages to console if file could not be read or located.

    • initializeAttendeeTable

      private void initializeAttendeeTable()
      Helper method, initializes columns in schedule attendees tableview.

    • syncTextBoxes

      private void syncTextBoxes(StudioManagerController.TabMode currentTab)
      Copies the information from the textfields and tableview from the Attendance/Registration tab to the other tab.
      Parameters:
      currentTab - flag used to determine which tab the user had recently input data from.

    • getProfile

      private Profile getProfile(StudioManagerController.TabMode mode)
      Attempts to create a profile from the textfields and date picker. Will return null if there is missing data or the DOB was invalid.
      Parameters:
      mode - flag used to determine which tab the user is on.
      Returns:
      a profile if the input was valid, null otherwise.

    • getMember

      private Member getMember(StudioManagerController.TabMode mode)
      Returns the corresponding member from the members list given the input from the textfields and datepicker.
      Parameters:
      mode - flag used to determine which tab the user is on.
      Returns:
      the member corresponding to the information entered, null if member was not in list.

    • getFitnessClass

      private FitnessClass getFitnessClass(StudioManagerController.TabMode mode)
      Returns the fitness class that was selected from either the schedule tableview or choicebox.
      Parameters:
      mode - flag used to determine which tab the user is on.
      Returns:
      the fitness class the user selected, null if user has not selected any option.

    • createMember

      private Member createMember(Profile profile, Location homeStudio)
      Creates a new member given a profile, location and the current membership type radiobutton that is selected.
      Parameters:
      profile - the profile of the new member.
      homeStudio - the home studio of the new member.
      Returns:
      a new member corresponding to the information provided on the registration tab.

    • initialize

      public void initialize()
      Fills and initializes all choiceboxes and tableviews in the GUI.

    • register

      public void register()
      Registers a new member to the members list. Will reject invalid input, members under 18 and will not add a member if they are already registered.

    • remove

      public void remove()
      Removes a member from the member list, does nothing if member was not registered.

    • check

      public void check()
      Checks the status of a given member's membership.

    • loadMembers

      private void loadMembers()
      Prompts the user to select a text file to load new members to the current member list.

    • loadSchedule

      private void loadSchedule()
      Prompts user to load a new class schedule given a properly formatted text file.

    • attend

      public void attend()
      Records the attendance of a member/guest given their information and a selected class. Will not add members/guest to list if there is a time conflict, location conflict, if they are already in the class or if they have no guest passes.

    • drop

      public void drop()
      Drops a member/guest from the currently selected class, adds back a guest pass if applicable. Will fail if member/guest is not attending the given class.

    • displayClassMemberList

      public void displayClassMemberList()
      Given a selected class on the schedule choicebox, will display all the members attending that class.

    • displayClassGuestList

      public void displayClassGuestList()
      Given a selected class on the schedule choicebox, will display all the guests attending that class.
